data.title: Listing all country codes of phone numbers
data.meta_description: I'd like to have the country code list for phone numbers. Such as, United State (+1), United Kingdom (+44) ... I know that libphonenumber is a great tool to help phone parsing, formatting and valid...

Phonelibnumber HAS built-in method which returns a Set of supported country codes.

Just call phoneNumberUtil.getSupportedCallingCodes().

(for instance, it will return you 1 for the US and 380 for Ukraine).

Then if you need you can iterate over them and get the region code:

String countryCode = phoneNumberUtil.getRegionCodeForCountryCode(codeFromThePreviousStep)

It will return you US and UA for the mentioned above countries.

If you need the country name - retrieve it from locale:

Locale locale = new Locale("", countryCode). String countryName = locale.getDisplayCountry()

That will give you United States and Ukraine accordingly

I suggest using PhoneNumberUtil along with java.util.Locale for getting the country name. You can import libphonenumber into your gradle file using: implementation 'com.googlecode.libphonenumber:libphonenumber:8.12.21'

I wrote a code in Kotlin to output the region, country code, and country. so you can take a look at its output.

Code:

val phoneNumberUtil = PhoneNumberUtil.getInstance() val set = phoneNumberUtil.supportedRegions val arr = set.toTypedArray() for (i in arr.indices) { val region = arr[i] val countryCode = phoneNumberUtil.getCountryCodeForRegion(region) val locale = Locale("en", region) print("${region} $countryCode ${locale.displayCountry}\n") }
